or individual literary and film narratives and new impulses for post-classical narratology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aConcepts. 0aDiscourse analysis, Narrative. 0aNarration (Rhetoric) 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 0aThought and thinking. 4aKognitionswissenschaft. 4aNarratologie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aNarratology.  acognitive narratology.1 aCOOK, AMY, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCOPLAND, SARAH, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDANCYGIER, BARBARA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDANNENBERG, HILARY, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFEYERSINGER, ERWIN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHAMILTON, CRAIG, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHARDING, JENNIFER RIDDLE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHARTNER, MARCUS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartner, Marcus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKILGORE, CHRISTOPHER D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOAKLEY, TODD, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQUENDLER, CHRISTIAN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aREDLING, ERIK, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSCHNEIDER, RALF, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSINDING, MICHAEL, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Ralf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTOBIN, VERA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBo